He told a Krishna Rabilal remembrance service on Friday: "Inexperienced cadres are often deployed to key positions as a reward for factional support and this has led to the hollowing out of leadership capacity. The crisis of leadership has become a crisis for all of us - for society as a whole."Rabilal, an ANC activist, was killed in Mozambique during the Matola Raid on January 30 1981.Jonas said state capacity had been eroded, with deployment being based on factional loyalty."Political faction fights infect nearly every organ of state and state-owned companies, and this has led to conflicts inside the bureaucracy and between politicians and bureaucrats."